title: TikTok Ramen
summary: TikTok Ramen takes approximately 12 minutes from beginning to end. One portion of this dish contains about 15g of protein, 24g of fat, and a total of 298 calories. For $1.0 per serving, you get a main course that serves 1. 1 person found this recipe to be scrumptious and satisfying. A mixture of brown sugar, scallions, cooking oil, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. Not a lot of people really liked this Japanese dish. It is a good option if you're following a gluten free diet. It is brought to you by Hungry Huy. Overall, this recipe earns an improvable spoonacular score of 0%. If you like this recipe, take a look at these similar recipes: TikTok Baked Feta Pasta, TikTok Green Goddess Salad, and TikTok Crinkle Dessert (Muakacha).

winePairing.pairingText: Ramen Noodles can be paired with Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. One wine you could try is J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling. It has 4.4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 22 dollars.

productMatches.title: J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling
productMatches.description:
Despite its still youthful freshness it shows the fine fruity Riesling characteristic and an underlying hint of mineral from the blue/grey Devonian slate soil.

Serve this refreshing wine slightly chilled! As aperitif and, especially when more matured, in combination with seafood or poultry.

instructions:
Cook noodles according to package instructions to al dente texture and then drain. Optionally if you want to cook the noodles and heat the sauce simultaneously, you can leave the noodles in the water and be ready to fish them out into the sauce pan (when its ready) so they don't overcook.

Preheat a small pan over medium-low heat for a little bit, then add the butter and garlic until very lightly browned. Then add the brown sugar and soy sauce. If you want spicier ramen, you can add the red pepper flakes at this point. Start with a pinch at a time and taste it.

Add the noodles and stir to evenly coat.

Push the noodles all the way to one side (or remove completely), add the oil and let it heat a bit. Crack eggs into a bowl, add salt and quickly whish with a whisk or fork. Pour in the eggs and scramble until cooked--I like mine still a bit jiggly inside. Brea it apart a bit then mix with the noodles.

Add Everything But The Bagel Seasoning and red pepper flakes to taste and serve immediately.
